article.headline: North Carolina Central slams Barber-Scotia 108-52
article.story: DURHAM, N.C. -- Jordan Parks landed a double-double, scoring 33 points and grabbing 10 rebounds to lead North Carolina Central to a 108-52 win over USCAA Barber-Scotia in an exhibition game on Wednesday night. Jeremiah Ingram added 15 points and seven rebounds for the Eagles (7-5). Jamal Ferguson and Nate Maxey each had 12 points and Nimrod Hilliard scored 10. NC Central outrebounded the Sabers 57-19 and buried them with 62.3 percent shooting from the field and 64 percent shooting from the line. The Eagles went 24-9 to start the game on their way to a 62-20 halftime lead. They opened the second period with an 11-3 run in the first four minutes to a 73-25 advantage and never looked back. Christopher Calvan scored 16 points with seven rebounds and two steals to lead the Sabers. Shaquille Wilson added 12.
